Of the 282 deaths, 66 were from Eastern Cape, 89 from Gauteng, 57 from KwaZulu-Natal, 3 from Northern Cape, 34 from Western Cape and 20 from North West and 13 from Free State. The Tuesday infection number  was recorded from 14 677  tests conducted in the last 24 hours, bringing the total number of tests conducted so far from 3 415 670 to 3430 347. Of the 592 144 infections, 485 468 patients have recovered from the deadly disease, shooting the recovery rate to 82 percent.  Ngwako Malatji